#  change        name    float

def change(df_feat, name):
    for i in tqdm(range(len(df_feat))):
        try:
            df_feat[name][i] = re.findall(r'\d+[\.\d+|\d+]', str(df_feat[name][i]))[0]
        except:
            df_feat[name][i] = df_feat[name][i]
    return df_feat[name].astype(float)

def scatterplot(x_data, y_data, x_label="", y_label="", title="", color = "r", yscale_log=False):

    _, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.scatter(x_data, y_data, s = 10, color = color, alpha = 0.75)

    if yscale_log == True:
        ax.set_yscale('log')

    ax.set_title(title)
    ax.set_xlabel(x_label)
    ax.set_ylabel(y_label)

from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression
from sklearn.metrics import r2_score, mean_squared_error as MSE
In [63]:
def FitPredict(model, X_train, y_train, X_test, y_test):
    
    model = model
    model.fit(X_train, y_train)

    pred_mse_train = pd.DataFrame(model.predict(X_train))
    pred_mse_test = pd.DataFrame(model.predict(X_test))
    
    print('MSE for train:', MSE(y_train, pred_mse_train))
    print('MSE for test:', MSE(y_test, pred_mse_test))

    print('r2_score for train', r2_score(y_train, pred_mse_train))
    print('r2_score for test', r2_score(y_test, pred_mse_test))

    print('  :', model.coef_)
    print(' :', model.intercept_)
    return model, pred_mse_train, pred_mse_test

def business_metrics(y_true, y_pred):
    summ = y_true.shape[0]
    col = 0
 
    y_pred = pd.DataFrame(y_pred)

    for i in range(summ):
        if abs(y_pred.iloc[i][0] - y_true.iloc[i][0]) / y_pred.iloc[i][0] <= 10:
            col =+ 1
    return col / summ * 100

print('   (%),        10%  train:', \
      round(business_metrics(y_train, pred_mse_train), 3))

print('   (%),        10%  test:', \
      round(business_metrics(y_test, pred_mse_test), 3))
